In this code, we define the two uniforms `rayStartY` and `rayEndY` which represent the coordinates of the starting point and ending point of the ray. These are used in the fragment shader to calculate the 3D position of each pixel on the screen.

The vertex shader simply passes the UV coordinate to the fragment shader. The fragment shader calculates the z depth of each pixel by subtracting the ray start y value from the ray end y value, multiplied by the UV y coordinate, and finally subtracting 1.0.

The x and y coordinates of the pixel are then calculated by multiplying the UV x and y coordinates by the z depth. This positions each pixel on the screen according to its distance along the ray. Finally, a white color is assigned to the fragment.

