```solidity
struct Credentials {
    uint256 id; // Unique identifier for each credential 
    string name; // Name of the credential
    string description; // Description of the credential
    address issuer; // Issuer of the credential
}
```

The smart contract would have a mapping of `address => credentials` which maps an address to their credentials. The contract would also have functions to mint, burn, transfer and revoke credentials.

Minting a new credential would require the caller to provide a valid `credentials` struct. The contract can then verify the signature of the issuer before minting the credential. 

```solidity
